This is just a question of errorprone, and doesn't have anything to do with pants. Does _errorprone_ have an option to take a classpath for the thing it is compiling? If so, you should use that option to pass the classpath in, rather than setting the classpath of the JVM that errorprone is running in.

Think of it this way: I can invoke javac directly like so:

    java -cp ${compiler-classpath} com.sun.tools.javac.Main -classpath ${sources-classpath} -d ${output} ${sources}

...and that's what you want to be doing here. *Instead*, what you are currently doing is:

    java -cp ${compiler-classpath}:${sources-classpath} com.sun.tools.javac.Main -d ${output} ${sources}

which is undesirable.

